To use Node.js&#39;s `require` function you must enable `webPreferences.nodeIntegration` in the `BrowserWindow` options.

Example:

    new BrowserWindow({
        webPreferences: {
            nodeIntegration: true,
        },
        // Other options here.
    });

[All BrowserWindow options](https://electronjs.org/docs/api/browser-window#new-browserwindowoptions). Search for `nodeIntegration`.

`nodeIntegration` used to be `true` by default. But in v5.0.0 they changed the default to `false`.

[Link to issue](https://github.com/electron/electron/issues/4362)

